Here's how to run everything:
  Ports
  ┌─────────────┬──────┬────────────────────────────┐
  │   Service   │ Port │            URL             │
  ├─────────────┼──────┼────────────────────────────┤
  │ Backend API │ 8000 │ http://localhost:8000      │
  ├─────────────┼──────┼────────────────────────────┤
  │ Frontend    │ 5173 │ http://localhost:5173      │
  ├─────────────┼──────┼────────────────────────────┤
  │ API Docs    │ 8000 │ http://localhost:8000/docs │
  └─────────────┴──────┴────────────────────────────┘
  ---
  Running the Backend

  cd D:\MyDocuments\Development\tradingbot\backend

  # Install dependencies (first time only)
  pip install -r requirements.txt

  # Run the server
  uvicorn app.main:app --reload --host 0.0.0.0 --port 8000

  ---
  Running the Frontend

  cd D:\MyDocuments\Development\tradingbot\frontend

  # Install dependencies (first time only)
  npm install

  # Run dev server
  npm run dev

  ---
  Running Tests

  Frontend tests (Vitest):
  cd D:\MyDocuments\Development\tradingbot\frontend
  npm test

  Backend tests (Pytest):
  cd D:\MyDocuments\Development\tradingbot\backend
  pytest

  ---
  Quick Start (Both Services)

  Open two terminals:

  Terminal 1 - Backend:
  cd D:\MyDocuments\Development\tradingbot\backend
  uvicorn app.main:app --reload

  Terminal 2 - Frontend:
  cd D:\MyDocuments\Development\tradingbot\frontend
  npm run dev

  Then open http://localhost:5173 in your browser.
  


---
  Configuration Files Summary

  Files You MUST Edit (for production)
  File: backend/config.yaml
  Purpose: Main backend config
  What to Configure: Exchange API keys, email settings
  ────────────────────────────────────────
  File: backend/data_sources.yaml
  Purpose: External data sources
  What to Configure: API keys, enable/disable sources
  backend/config.yaml - Key Settings:

  server:
    host: "0.0.0.0"      # Keep as-is
    port: 8000           # Backend port

  exchange:
    api_key: ""          # YOUR EXCHANGE API KEY
    api_secret: ""       # YOUR EXCHANGE SECRET
    sandbox_mode: true   # Set false for live trading

  email:
    enabled: false       # Set true to enable alerts
    smtp_host: ""        # e.g., smtp.gmail.com
    smtp_port: 587
    smtp_user: ""        # Your email
    smtp_password: ""    # Your email password/app key
    from_address: ""
    to_address: ""       # Alert recipient

  backend/data_sources.yaml - External Data:

  sources:
    fear_greed:
      enabled: false     # Set true to enable (free, no API key)

    market_conditions:
      enabled: false     # Set true to enable (free CoinGecko)

    news_api:
      enabled: false
      api_key: ""        # Get from https://newsapi.org/

    # These need paid APIs in production:
    onchain_metrics:
      enabled: false
      api_key: ""

    social_sentiment:
      enabled: false
      api_key: ""

  ---
  Quick Start Checklist

  1. Install dependencies:
  # Backend
  cd backend
  pip install -r requirements.txt

  # Frontend
  cd frontend
  npm install
  2. Configure (minimum for dev):
    - backend/config.yaml - No changes needed for dry-run mode
    - backend/data_sources.yaml - Enable fear_greed and market_conditions if you want
  external data
  3. Run:
  # Terminal 1 - Backend
  cd backend
  uvicorn app.main:app --reload

  # Terminal 2 - Frontend
  cd frontend
  npm run dev
  4. Access:
    - Frontend: http://localhost:5173
    - API Docs: http://localhost:8000/docs

